    "It is analytically useful because it clarifies the structure of the residual stream [10], which describes how transformers may use orthogonal subspaces of layer outputs as communication channels.",
    "In particular, while standard transformers store information in orthogonal subspaces of the residual stream, disentangled transformers store the outputs of each layer in separate matrix blocks.",
    "We will refer to h (i) as the residual stream at layer i.",
    "Throughout this paper, we will analyze disentangled transformers.",
    "For simplicity, we will consider transformers with a single head."
